      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.xiaohuangyu.space/en/p/ai-powering-dreams-part-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In my previous post &lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.xiaohuangyu.space/2026/03/25/AI-%E5%8A%A9%E5%8A%9B%E6%AF%8F%E4%B8%80%E4%B8%AA%E6%A2%A6%E6%83%B3/&#34;&gt;AI-Powering Dreams&lt;/a&gt;, I documented my experience using Claude Code with glm5 to build a cross-platform skill management tool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This time, I set my sights on my own blog. With AI assistance, I completed a series of improvements in just 12 hours that I previously found too complex or troublesome to tackle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;transformation-checklist&#34;&gt;Transformation Checklist&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s what was accomplished:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;theme-migration&#34;&gt;Theme Migration&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Switched from my old theme to &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/adityatelange/hugo-PaperMod&#34;&gt;PaperMod&lt;/a&gt;, which offers:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
